&lt;p&gt;A StackOverflowError basically is when you try to do something, that most likely calls itself, and goes on for infinity (or until it gives a StackOverflowError).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;add5(a)&lt;/code&gt; will call itself, and then call itself again, and so on.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a typical case of &lt;code&gt;java.lang.StackOverflowError&lt;/code&gt;... The method is recursively calling itself with no exit in &lt;code&gt;doubleValue()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;floatValue()&lt;/code&gt;, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
